Well-known for its sprawling forest of stone peaks, a distinctive landscape in central China, Zhangjiajie National Forest Park was engulfed in mist following a spring shower on February 19. Clusters of peaks encircled by a sea of clouds are reminiscent of a floating castle complex in a fantasy realm. (Video provided by Zhang Hongtao) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)